_No response_

### Other cases

Works with `match` statement instead of `if let`:

```Rust
fn main() {
	let bytes: &'static str;
	let file: Result<&str, &str> = Ok("File data");

	match file {
	    Ok(store) => bytes = store,
	    Err(_err) => std::process::exit(1),
	}
	
	println!("{}", bytes);
}
```


### Anything else?

Tested on rust playground using stable rustc 1.69.0.
